# Alembic Database Migrations

This directory contains the database migration scripts for the Portfolio Backend API using [Alembic](https://alembic.sqlalchemy.org/).

## Overview
Alembic tracks changes to the SQLAlchemy models and applies those changes to the database incrementally. This ensures your database schema stays in sync with your codebase over time without manually executing SQL scripts.

## Common Commands

Run these commands from the root of the `backend` directory.

### 1. Create a New Migration (Autogenerate)
After making changes to any SQLAlchemy models (e.g. in `app/modules/projects/models.py`), generate a new migration script automatically:

```bash
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "Add short description of your changes"
```
*Note: Always review the generated script in `alembic/versions/` to ensure Alembic caught all your model changes correctly.*

### 2. Apply Migrations to the Database
To apply all pending migrations and update your database schema to the latest version:

```bash
alembic upgrade head
```

### 3. Rollback Migrations
If you need to undo the last migration:

```bash
alembic downgrade -1
```

### 4. View Migration History
To see the current state of the database and the migration history:

```bash
alembic history
```

## Directory Structure
- `env.py`: The Python script run by Alembic whenever a migration is invoked. It connects to the database and provides the model metadata.
- `script.py.mako`: The template used to generate new migration scripts.
- `versions/`: This folder holds all the actual migration scripts (the version history).